snippet.textDisplay: In my book, the trash can Mac Pro is how to make a high efficiency computer because it actually takes advantages of custom made hardware and cools all of them with one simple airflow, with great function and form, the new Mac Pro is a regression in terms of space and material efficiency in my opinion but it allows for custom expansion, so still not too bad. While this PC is a beast I don't see the point, it uses standard PC parts but there's no room left for custom expansion, and it can't be made to the same level of space efficiency like with custom hardware, it's full of tubes and wires that could be a maintenance nightmare if anything goes wrong, and to add to all of that, it's not good looking.
snippet.textOriginal: In my book, the trash can Mac Pro is how to make a high efficiency computer because it actually takes advantages of custom made hardware and cools all of them with one simple airflow, with great function and form, the new Mac Pro is a regression in terms of space and material efficiency in my opinion but it allows for custom expansion, so still not too bad.
